
1. Create POSTGRESQL database
$ su postgres
$ createuser akp
$ createdb -E UTF8 -O akp akp

2. Configure APACHE
$ cp akp/conf/001-akp.conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/
$ ln -s ../sites-available/001-akp.conf /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/001-akp
$ /etc/init.d/apache restart

3. Build AKP
$ cd akp
$ gradle assemble

4. Install AKP
$ cp build/distributions/akp-x.y.z.zip /opt
$ cd /opt && unzip -o akp*.zip
$ cp conf/log4j.properties /opt/akp-x.y.z/
$ cp conf/akp.params /opt/akp-x.y.z/

Create an init script to run AKP, that launch the following cmd:

cd /opt/akp-x.y.z && ./bin/akp @akp.params

4. Configure APACHE REDIRECTION
$ vi /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
In <Directory> "/var/www/" conf add: AllowOverride All
Add .htaccess file in /var/www/akp containing:
RedirectMatch 301 ^.*$ http://www2.plantkelt.net/akp/web/

